</div></div></div></div><div class="node-body"><div class="panel-pane pane-entity-field pane-node-body" ><div class="pane-content"><div class="field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even" property="content:encoded"><p><strong>Do our genes control how we respond to COVID? The question has been nagging at the world since the pandemic began. Now we have the answer - and it's yes. In this programme, geneticist Nathan Pearson uncovers the specific bits of DNA that make you more likely to catch coronavirus, as well as the bits that might make you sicker....</strong></p></div></div></div></div></div><div class="panel-separator"></div><div class="panel-pane pane-block pane-adsense-managed-2 pane-adsense-managed responsive width-728" ><div class="pane-content"><div style='text-align:center'><div class='adsense responsive' >
